    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Buffalo Wings</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 pounds chicken wings, split at joints, tips discarded</li>
            <li>1 cup all-purpose flour</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon garlic powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon onion powder</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon cayenne pepper</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li>
            <li>1/4 teaspoon black pepper</li>
            <li>1/2 cup unsalted butter</li>
            <li>1/2 cup hot sauce (such as Frank's RedHot)</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon honey</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce</li>
            <li>Blue cheese dressing and celery sticks for serving</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>appetizer</li>
            <li>spicy</li>
            <li>chicken</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).</li>
            <li>In a large bowl, combine flour, garlic powder, onion powder, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper.</li>
            <li>Dredge the chicken wings in the flour mixture, shaking off excess.</li>
            <li>Place a wire rack on a baking sheet and arrange the wings on the rack. Bake for 45-50 minutes or until golden brown and crispy.</li>
            <li>In a saucepan over medium heat, melt butter. Stir in hot sauce, honey, and Worcestershire sauce. Simmer for a few minutes, stirring occasionally.</li>
            <li>In a large bowl, toss the baked wings in the buffalo sauce until well coated.</li>
            <li>Serve the Buffalo Wings with blue cheese dressing and celery sticks on the side.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your spicy and flavorful Buffalo Wings!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
